research_municipality_step.notes: The City of Selma, TX, is governed by a mayor and a five-member City Council under the general law type A format. The roles 'Place Three', 'Place Four', 'Place Five', and 'Place Six' refer to specific council seats rather than geographical divisions. There was a discrepancy in one source regarding the Mayor Pro Tem role for Jim Parma, but the official city website and Texas Municipal League directory confirm Noah Washington Jr. as Mayor Pro-Tem and Jim Parma as Council Member Place Five.
